items.name: Dandelion | The Witcher 3 : Wild Hunt
items.description:
Character Lora of Dandelion from The Witcher 3 : Wild Hunt

"Famous last words right there" -Dandelion

Stay out of trouble for five minutes ya daft bard -soul3142


This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International License.

If you want to, you can support me on Patreon or Buy me Coffee.

My Witcher LoRA Index - soul3142's Guide to the Witcher Universe. additionally you can check out some characters i've made from other games also.

Main Trigger Word - dandelionW3_soul3142 , check examples for other ones.

RECOMMENDATIONS :-

  1. Highres Fix - must, if you are getting blurry and ugly images

    My upscale method: txt2img 512x768 -> send to img2img -> controlnet tile upscale, tile diffusion 2x scale with 4xUltrasharp upscaler and tiled vae

  2. Weight: 0.6 - 0.8

  3. Clip Skip: 2

  4. Denoising - Don't go too high, it can alter a lot of details

  5. For better face's - you can use ADetailer

I use 0.7 weight, 25 steps, Euler a, Clip skip 2 in nearly all my examples with almost same, simple +ve/-ve prompts regardless of checkpoint for my own consistency purposes.

There are imperfections here & there, which i usually leave it in as is, (i never do any inpainting in examples), most of which like hands can be fixed with better prompting, negative embeddings while other like weapons are just bad majority of the time no matter the model as of today.

Some LoRA's are flexible with any clothing, some are not (usually character's with single costume) so keep these things in mind.

This is an unofficial fanmade LoRA, not intended for any commercial purpose and use. All characters and IP rights are owned by their respective creators and owners. I do not own rights to any of these characters.

items.name: Elon Musk (Current Day) - HQ Dreambooth Trained
items.description:
High Quality Dreambooth (JP's repo / 24gb-Vram) trained checkpoint of Elon Musk using recently taken HD photographs from news/media sites.

There are a couple LORAs of Musk on Civitai, but imho the likeness achieved by this checkpoint will out perform any Lora model. Providing the full 2gb checkpoint (vs. an extracted / lossy LoRA file) will give you the best quality. If a CKPT for one likeness isn't practical/useful for your workflow then go check out the LoRA versions - please don't comment in regards to the fornat - this is for those w resources who want top quality. It's fairly easy to extract a Lora from checkpoints using various A1111 extensions (For example"Supermerger" is the one I use). If you do make a Lora from this checkpoint please keep it for personal use and don't circulated it in an extracted (lossy) format.

Use Hi-Res fix with a denoise strength in the .2 range for best results. For optimal results use with the Controlnet extension (w/ a model like Openpose or Canny cutting off before the final step)

Most of the examples were generated w/ controlnet so you won't be able to replicate them (w/o the image I used to initiate the generation). Also, I renamed the file prior to uploading but all of the samples were generated w/ this model (even if the info shows a different name).

items.name: GAME DEV TOOLS 03 / TOPO
items.description:
If you find our articles informative, please follow me to receive updates. It would be even better if you could also follow our ko-fi, where there are many more articles and tutorials that I believe would be very beneficial for you!

如果你觉得我们的文章有料，请关注我获得更新通知，
如果能同时关注我们的 ko-fi 就更好了，
那里有多得多的文章和教程! 相信能使您获益良多.

For collaboration and article reprint inquiries, please send an email to aigarlic@pm.me
合作和文章转载 请发送邮件至 aigarlic@pm.me

By: Ash0080

English

About V4

Actually, when I was training this model, I named it V3Fix because its training dataset is exactly the same as V3, but I fixed some errors. However, it was trained using a completely different strategy, and now it is a style-agnostic LoRa model with very minimal impact on the style of the base model.

Therefore, it can now be applied to almost all types of base models, including 2D, 2.5D, 3D, and Photo. Moreover, you no longer need two models, whether it is for txt2Img or img2img. One model is enough. because its usage has undergone such a significant change. To avoid confusion, I renamed it V4.

For V4, setting the weight to 1 is sufficient. Reducing this weight can to some extent weaken the strength of the lines (but may also cause loss of lines), and I recommend between 1 and 0.7.

For other features, such as HiRes, face correction, and using tips, please refer to the V3 instructions for now. By the way, the Hires Denoising Strength is no longer limited to 0.33, so you can use larger values more normally.

Img2Img has been greatly improved because it is much more tolerant of image style than V3. Now, it is much better at applying topology to images.

What?

This is an experimental model that serves as a tool for adding topology lines to models. Its ultimate goal is to bring everything into a 3D world. ( although that's still quite far away )

Perhaps in the future, it could be combined with NERF to create something amazing, but I don't know for sure!

Why?

Having worked in the gaming industry for many years, although I am no longer a practitioner in the art-related fields, I still believe that AI has the potential to offer much more in game development. Of course, this does not mean that AI can replace excellent artists, but I believe it can help them reduce some of the repetitive work in their daily tasks. This series of GAME DEV TOOLS is based on this idea.

Topology is a crucial skill that 3D modelers need to master, and professional practitioners even use the quality of topology to judge whether a modeler is a novice or an expert. This is not a secret in the industry. However, even for very experienced modelers, they will often keep some topology diagrams as a reference, which can indeed improve efficiency and reduce errors. Therefore, I attempted to create this tool, hoping that AI can learn topology.

Fortunately, I succeeded (to some extent).

TXT2IMG & IMG2IMG

This tool is divided into two models, one for text-to-image and the other for image-to-image.

How to use it

TXT2IMG is relatively straightforward. The canvas size should be around 1024 pixels on one side, such as 1024x1024, 768x1024, 1024x768, etc.

If it is a close-up, it can be reduced to around 768 pixels. Because wireframe needs enough pixels to be drawn clearly,

add wireframe, <lora:topo_v3_t2i:0.6> to the end of your prompt.

If you try other models, the lora weight will suggest between 0.6-0.9, but it is best not to exceed 0.9.

IMG2IMG is a bit more complex. I am currently only sharing some images, which were all searched from Google. It needs to be used with ControlNet, and I will write a separate tutorial and come back to update the link later.

(updated tutorials)

A more detailed tutorial for txt2img

https://civitai.com/articles/1065/can-lora-learn-topology

Use Guide for img2img

https://civitai.com/articles/1110/user-guide-for-topology-img2img

Capabilities

You can use high-res! 0.33~0.44

You can use ADetailer to retouch the face! (If you are drawing a full-body picture, you may need to use it.)

It can draw a gray model by adding "monochrome" to positive prompts.

It can draw a color model by adding "monochrome" to negative prompts.

It can change the wireframe color to some extent by using "green_skin", "red_skin" and similar prompts (not perfect).

Model Selection

As it is a style model, all models are suitable, even 2D models. However, the 2.5D model without noise offset works best (I must say that I have some objections to the current proliferation of noise offset, and I hope everyone can reduce its use, especially when training Lora, because I found that it will overlap with the model and make the picture dirty. It can be said that there is no reason to use it in 90% of LoRa training! This was originally a very good invention, but it has been abused by many people who do not understand it, which is very regrettable.)

I can't draw what I want?

Because it is LoRa, it has very significant limitations. Currently, TXT2IMG can draw things including but not limited to girl, boy, dog, pig, frog, rabbit, Mandalorian. It is almost impossible to draw any mecha content (it will become a completely different style).

However, IMG2IMG can have a broader range of applications, but its drawing quality is relatively lower (because it is IMG2IMG).

You can help me make it more useful

I am looking forward to more professional collaboration. Although the IMG2IMG model can meet some work requirements and make it more like a tool, even if I try to minimize the influence of the style, I cannot completely eliminate it. This is a limitation of LoRa itself. Therefore, I am looking forward to collaborating with professional game development teams so that I can create models that are more in line with actual needs and further improve their quality and functionality (such as... many ideas).

中文

关于V4

这个其实在我训练的时候我给它起名叫V3Fix, 因为它的训练集数据和V3完全相同，我只是修复了一点错误。不过，它是用完全不同的方法训练，它现在是一个去风格化的LoRa模型，对底模的style影响微乎其微。

因此它现在可以被套用在几乎所有类型的底模上，包括2D, 2.5D, 3D, Photo, 并且，你不再需要两个模型，无论是txt2Img还是img2img, 一个模型就可以了, 因为它的使用方式发生了如此大的改变，我还是将它重命名为V4比较好吧，避免造成大家的混淆。

V4的权重给1就好了， 减小该权重可以一定程度上减弱线条的强度（但也可能会造成线条丢失)，推荐1~0.7之间，其它包括 HiRes，修脸，使用tip，暂时请参照V3说明，我之后有空会再补充个教程。

Img2Img得到了非常大的改善，因为它对图片风格的宽容度比V3强太多了， 现在它变得更擅长给图片套上topology

是什么？

这是一个实验模型, 用来给模型添加拓扑线的工具。将一切都拉入3D世界（虽然这个目标还很遥远）

也许未来可以与nerf结合做点什么？ 我不知道

为什么？

我曾经在游戏行业工作了许多年，虽然我现在早已不再是一个美术相关的从业者，但我仍然觉得AI在游戏开发中，应该存在着更多的可能性，当然这并不意味着AI可以取代那些优秀的艺术家，但我认为AI可以帮助他们减少一些日常工作中的重复性劳动，这个GAME DEV TOOLS系列都是基于这一想法而产生的一系列工具。

TOPOLOGY是3D模型师需要掌握的一个非常重要的技能，专业从业者甚至通过拓扑的好坏来判断一个模型师是新手还是老手，这并不是什么行业秘密。不过即使对于非常成熟的模型师来说，往往也会将一些拓扑图放在手边作为参考，这确实能提升工作效率和减少出错。因此，我尝试做了这个工具，希望让AI能学会拓扑。

TXT2IMG & IMG2IMG

这个工具分成两个模型， 分别用于文生图和图生图，

使用

TXT2IMG比较简单，画幅单边在1024左右，比如1024x1024, 768x1024, 1024x768等等，

如果是close_up可以降低到768左右。因为wirefame需要足够的像素才能画得清楚

在你的prompts末尾添加: wireframe, <lora:topo_v3_t2i:0.6>

如果你尝试其它模型，那么lora权重会建议在0.6~0.9, 但是最好不要超过0.9

IMG2IMG稍微复杂一些，我暂时只放一些图，这些原图都是从google中搜索的。

需要搭配ControlNet, 我会单独写一篇教程，晚点回来更新链接

能力

可以Hires！ 0.33~0.44

可以ADetailer修脸！(如果你画的是full_body, 你很可能会需要用到它)

可以画灰色模型，在positive中加入 monochrome

可以画彩色模型，在negative中加入monochrome

可以一定程度改变wireframe颜色， 使用green_skin, red_skin之类的（不是很完美）

模型选择

因为是style模型，所有模型都适用，甚至2D模型也可以，

不过2.5D模型, 不带noise offset的模型效果最佳（插一句，我对目前泛滥的Noise Offset颇有意见，我希望大家能减少它的使用，尤其是训练lora不要使用，因为我发现它会与模型叠加，让画面变脏，可以说90%的LoRa训练都没理由用到它! 这本来是一个非常好的发明，但被很多不明所以的人滥用了，非常可惜。）

我想画的东西画不出？

因为它是LoRa，它有非常大的局限性，

TXT2IMG目前可以画的东西包括但不限于，

girl, boy, dog, pig, frog, rabbit, mandalorian

目前几乎不能画任何mecha内容（它会变成别的完全不同的风格）

但IMG2IMG可以有更宽泛的应用，但它的绘制质量要差一些（因为是IMG2IMG）

你可以帮助我将它做得更好

我期待更专业的合作，尽管IMG2IMG模型能够满足一些工作需求，让它更像个工具。但即使我尽可能的减弱风格的影响，但我没法完全消除它，这是LoRa本身局限。所以我期待着与专业游戏开发团队的合作，这样我可以做出更符合实际需要的风格的模型，也可以更进一步提升它的品质和功能（比如... 更多)

items.name: painterly-XL
items.description:
A LoCon model for creating a more painterly, impressionist style for the base SDXL 0.9 model. In some cases, it may be better to not run the refiner model on the outputs, as it changes the art style a bit. Gonna update this thing when SDXL 1.0 releases, or, obviously, when I do more training. Have fun!

For best results, I recommend to start your prompt with "a painterly illustration of..." or "a digital painting of...". This guides the model to create a less detailed, softer appearance.

This model is designed for use with SDXL, and will not work with SD 1.5, 2.1, or any other version.

This version is a re-training based on normal LoCon, trained on the same dataset for 50 epochs, and then further fine-tuned on just the term "digital art" for another 20. This model produces similar results, and may be consistent than the original one. Also, 300 megs -> 18!

items.name: Betty Gilpin PhotoRealistic
items.description:
Suggested settings:

Positive: <lora:betty_gelpin_lora_v1:1> betty_gilpin, 1girl, solo, blonde hair, long hair, looking at viewer,

Negative: (empty to start, add nsfw if desired)

Clip Skip: 1

Resolution: 768x512

pretty tolerant of other settings - 7 cfg, 20 steps, 0.2 denoise for high res if you use it.

CLIP SKIP 1 is MUCH BETTER on some models, and slightly better on most models. If you really need clip skip 2 for some other reason, I'd suggest running it through a second pass at clip skip 1 just doing the face with the suggested starting prompt.

164 images, 28k steps, mostly 768x512, but many 512x512 and 512x768 as well.

Trigger word: betty_gilpin

Most common tags in data set: 1girl, solo, blonde hair, long hair, looking at viewer,

I tried a couple times to get this right, honed in on just the right amount of training at a very low learning rate for 3.5 hours on a 3090 ti. Removed the word 'realistic' from the tags in the training set. Few tags needed for realism and few negative tags needed as well. I suggest you start with just the trigger word and popular tags and start from there. Add nsfw into the negative prompt if you want to ensure that.

If you find you need them (if you're getting deformations and crazy stuff), here are a few negative embeddings I liked (one at a time, of course):

ng_deepnegative_v1_75t

BadNegAnatomyV1-neg

negative_hand-neg

bad_prompt_version2-neg

items.name: Кирилл, Святейший Патриарх Московский и всея Руси |  Patriarch Kirill of Moscow and all Rus' and Primate of the Russian Orthodox Church
items.description:
Кирилл, Святейший Патриарх Московский и всея Руси

Для создания LoRa использовались фотографии Патриарха Кирилла с официального сайта патриархии, которые были обрезаны и отмасштабированы до разрешения 768x768 пикс.

Версия v20700 обучалась на 20700 шагах, и она выглядит несколько "переобученной", стремясь все превратить в Патриарха. Крайне рекомендую устанавливать вес данной версии LoRa в диапазоне 0.25-0.7, обычно будет достаточно среднего значения в этом диапазоне.

Версия v1656 была обучена на 1656 шагах. Рекомендуется устанавливать вес данной версии LoRa в диапазоне 0.4-0.9. Просто поэкспериментируй с весами.

Если хочешь попробовать сделать лучше - используй эти изображения для тренировки.

Below is the translation in your Barbarian language:

Patriarch Kirill of Moscow and all Rus' and Primate of the Russian Orthodox Church

LoRa was created using photos of Patriarch Kirill from the official Patriarchate website, cropped and scaled to a resolution of 768x768 pixels.

Version 20700 has been trained for 20700 steps and seems to be somewhat "overtrained" as it tends to turn everything into Patriarch Kirill. It's highly recommended to set the weight of this LoRa version in the range of 0.25-0.7. Usually an average value in this range is sufficient.

Version 1656 has been trained for 1656 steps. It's recommended to set the weight of this LoRa version in the range of 0.4-0.9. Just experiment with the weights.

If you want to try and improve, you can use these pictures for training.

Данная версия обучалась на 20700 шагах, и поэтому она выглядит "переобученной", стремясь все превратить в Патриарха. Крайне рекомендую устанавливать вес данной версии LoRa в диапазоне 0.25-0.7, обычно будет достаточно среднего значения в этом диапазоне, просто поэкспериментируй.

items.name: Sort LyCORIS from LORA script
items.description:
I often dump everything I download in the lora folder. Turns out the LyCORIS models are supposed to go in a different folder.

I wrote this python script to find all the LyCORIS that were placed in the wrong folder.

e.g.

> python.exe find_lyco.py D:\\stable-diffusion-webui\\models\\lora
----------------------------------
| Looking for .safetensors files |
----------------------------------
D:\stable-diffusion-webui\models\lora\a.safetensors
D:\stable-diffusion-webui\models\lora\subdir\b.safetensors
D:\stable-diffusion-webui\models\lora\c.safetensors
----------------------------------

Main Trigger Word - eredinW3_soul3142 , check examples for other ones.

RECOMMENDATIONS :-

  1. Highres Fix - must, if you are getting blurry and ugly images

    My upscale method: txt2img 512x768 -> send to img2img -> controlnet tile upscale, tile diffusion 2x scale with 4xUltrasharp upscaler and tiled vae

  2. Weight: 0.6 - 0.8

  3. Clip Skip: 2

  4. Denoising - Don't go too high, it can alter a lot of details

  5. For better face's - you can use ADetailer

There are imperfections here & there, which i usually leave it in as is, (i never do any inpainting in examples), most of which like hands can be fixed with better prompting, negative embeddings while other like weapons are just bad majority of the time no matter the model as of today.

Some LoRA's are flexible with any clothing, some are not (usually character's with single costume) so keep these things in mind.

items.name: The Anime Wondermix
items.description:
V3

(Fp16 is coming soon)

The base for this version is very different from the first two. it took me time to get to where it is, but i'm very satisfied with the result. It's not perfect, but very well made in the end.

Why i'm very satisfied? Because i made it with in my head the idea of not using TI/Negative Embeddings anymore, and here the result : i'm very happy with it ^^

So yeah, all the output were generated with only one long Negative prompt and only a Negative Prompt (No TI/embeddings, LoRa, addetailer etc.... nothing)

The baked Vae is Blessed2

Generation Settings.

  • Sampler : DPM++ 2M karras

  • Sampling Steps : 20 to 40 (You get good result at 20 and awesome at 40.... going over 40 is not really usefull and a bit overkill).

  • CFG Scale : 8

  • Hires Fix : Feel free to use. But i don't know how it will behave because i didn't got the feeling of needing it. So i didn't tested it.

  • Clip Skip : 2

  • Upscaler : R-ESRGAN 4x++

Prompt Tips.

Positive : (masterpiece, best quality, absurdres, ultra detailed, intricate details, beautiful, finely detailed:1.5)

Negative : (worst quality, low quality),normal quality, lowres, jpeg artifacts, aliasing, monochrome, greyscale, text, signature, watermark, username, blurry, error, what, poorly drawn, deformed, image sample, sketch, duplicate, gif artifacts, scan scan artifacts, crease, bleed through, bad bad aspect ratio, what, bad anatomy, bad arm, bad feet, bad face, bad hands, bad leg, bad multiple views, multiple views, bad neck, bad proportions, bad perspective, bad reflection, bad vulva, bad labia, bad penis, bad testicles, bad ass, body horror, anatomical nonsense, engineering_nonsense, extra digits, fewer digits, fused fingers, ugly, put of frame, mutated, mutation, bad joints, poorly detailed, bad nose, bad lips, bad ears, bad hair, bad public hair, bad nipples, bad areolae, bad breats size, bad colors, bad clothes, simple background, bad object, bad background, gross proportions, cropped, extra legs, extra arms, missing limb, bad teeth, misplaced genitals, bad eyelashes, bad eyebrows, bad fingernails, bad pupils, bad iris, poor lighting, bad details, bad navel, bad thighs, bad wrists, bad ankles, bad toes, bad anus, bad tongue, bad clitoris, bad muscles, bad skin, wrong breasts size, wrong hairstyle, wrong hair color, wrong hair length, wrong clothes color, wrong pubic hair color, bad knees, bad elbows, bad shoulders, bad collarbone, bad shadow, bad lighting, bad details, fused limbs

About this Negative Prompt, it work very well on a lot of anime and 2.5D model. So feel free to use it :)

But forget it for realistic model..... while the body and background look great, the face look like sh*t <<

Enjoy ^^

V2

There is some bigdifference between the V1 and he V2.

The first one being the base. Instead of Counterfeit V3.0 and BeenYou Lite L11, i used a base of Counterfeit V3.0 and BeenYou Lite L15.

The second is : the fp16 version lose too much detailfor my taste, so only fp32 this time (you can try to convert it to fp16 if you want but, i advise against).

For the third and fourth one, we will get to it later.

Generation Settings.

The same as the V1

  • Sampler : DPM++ 2M karras

  • Sampling Steps : 20

  • CFG Scale : 7

  • Hires Fix : Feel free to use, but it's not mandatory.

  • Clip Skip : 2

  • Upscaler : R-ESRGAN 4x+ ANIME6B.

Third difference, which is not realyy one : i advise to use Adetailer with face_yolov8n when the character ist oo far. The eyes have tendencies to lose details around full body.

I advise to use this add-on whenever you feel the need on every other model around. It's really awesome. This is why it's not really a difference ;)

Prompt Tips.

Positive : masterpiece), best quality, highres, ultra-detailed.

And here come tle fourth difference..... unlike my other version (for each model), badhandv4 and EasyNegative, change the style too much on this one. It tookme a day too figure out a negative Prompt that doesn't change the style too much and still make the output look good. I found a good result, except for the hands. It's harder to ger good one without altering the model style too much.

Negative : negative_hand-neg, verybadimagenegative_v1.3, (worst quality), (low quality), normal quality, lowres, blurry, aliasing, jpeg artifacts, watermark, monochrome, greyscale, username, signature, error, poorly drawn, fewer digits, extra digits, bad vulva, misplaced genitals, poorly drawn eyes, comic, silent comic, poorly drawn ears, what, wrong hand, wrong feet, bad perspective, bad hands, bad feet, fused fingers, deformed, ugly, mutated hands, mutated fingers, poorly drawn hands, poorly drawn fingers, extra legs, extra arms, missing limb, bad proportions,

yup, it's a long one <<.

But, really, you get really good result, except for the hands on which you get good hands on an average rate.

Still, enjoy :)

About The Anime Wondermix V1

Hello everyone! It's me again ^^

So, this time, it's an anime model i present you.

More exactly, an anime version of The Wondermix.

They share the same base : Counterfeit V3.0 and the removed BeenYou Lite R11.

I just merged different model and in a different way, with only 1 realistic model.... But they still have a similar look.

Ok, i know i disgress ^^;

So about the model itself. It's a detailed anime model, capable of generating beautiful backdround, male characters and, of course, cute and petite to sexy and curvy female characters (muscular and chuby one included.... I don't discriminate!). There is also a very good range of different clothes. making it fun to create different outfit.

it's NSFW content compliable (well... you know... in my country there is a saying : Le cul fait vendre XD... Oh it's in French BTW).

LoRa work well with it. Character and style one included.

The baked VAE is Blessed2.

Generation Settings.

They are almost the same as The Wondermix, except for one.

  • Sampler : DPM++ 2M karras

  • Sampling Steps : 20

  • CFG Scale : 7

  • Hires Fix : Feel free to use, but it's not mandatory.

  • Clip Skip : 2

  • Upscaler : R-ESRGAN 4x+ ANIME6B (here is the difference).

Prompt Tips.

cough they are the sames as The Wondermix :D.

Positive : masterpiece), best quality, highres, ultra-detailed.

Negative : badhandv4, EasyNegative, verybadimagenegative_v1.3, monochrome, jpeg artifacts, text, watermark, signature, (worst quality), (low quality), (normal quality), lowres, greyscale, multiple views, comic, silent comic, extra digits, fewer digits,

The body have very good proportions, and getting error (fused limbs etc...) are rare, still occur from time to time, but rare.

Hands are still a problems. Not a big one, but the cases of bad hands and fingers still occurs too much for my taste.

Specifics Tags can yield some interesting result. While Anime or Manga style does nothing, the combo of realistic, phtoorealistic or the 3d tag are fun to use since.... the output look close to The Wondermix. pastel colors work well.

Credits.

I want to thanks rqdwdw and Bradcatt for their awesome works and models

Hope you'll enjoy and have fun with this model :)
